– 2 –
8 allow for the installation and use of a school bus infraction detection system in
9 school buses owned by the school district to enforce existing provisions of law
10 prohibiting a driver of any vehicle from overtaking or passing a school bus which:
11 (1) has stopped to receive or discharge any pupil; and (2) is displaying a flashing
12 red light signal visible from the front and rear. (NRS 484B.353) Section 2 requires
13 a peace officer of a traffic enforcement agency with jurisdiction over the location in
14 which any school bus equipped with such a system operates to review the evidence
15 of such a violation recorded by the system before a civil infraction citation is
16 issued. Section 2 further: (1) requires a school district that has not previously
17 installed and used a school bus infraction detection system to conduct a public
18 awareness campaign for not less than 30 days after the system is placed into use;
19 (2) establishes certain requirements for a hearing for a citation issued pursuant to
20 section 2; (3) applies an existing fine structure to a citation issued pursuant
21 to section 2; (4) requires a school district to use any fines collected pursuant to
22 section 2 for certain purposes; and (5) requires each school district that installs such
23 a system to prepare and submit an annual report to the Legislature relating to the
24 school bus infraction detection system. Sections 1 and 2 of this bill provide that a
25 violation detected by a school bus infraction detection system is not a moving
26 traffic violation.
27 Sections 1 and 4-6 of this bill make conforming changes to: (1) exclude traffic
28 violations detected by a school bus infraction detection system from the assessment
29 of demerit points; and (2) provide for the issuance of civil infraction citations for
30 violations detected by a school bus infraction detection system.
